title: Hillsborough County News Summary
summary: A 14-year-old boy was rescued from Tampa floodwaters after Hurricane Milton, thanks to a vigilant sheriff deputy. In Florida, multiple airports were closed due to the hurricane. Meanwhile, Chick-fil-A plans to replace a demolished Exxon in Hillsborough, New Jersey, and a street takeover involving 250 cars accumulated a huge audience in Montgomery. In other news, a police officer was arrested for video voyeurism in a shocking case, while a homeless, repeated sex offender in Concord was apprehended again. Florida has seen political drama as a prosecutor was suspended, impacting Governor Desantis's reelection campaign. Lastly, ex-Lions CB Cameron Sutton retired from professional football.
